              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">John's Review:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1"><p>This is one of the most remarkable collections of wildlife photos that I've ever seen. Matthew calls this book the "whaaaale" book. 
<br><br><p>We spend some time every day going through the pictures in this book - and Matthew identifies more and more every day. From whales to "aw aw" (gulls, and other birds with long beaks) to "turtle" to "ee ee" (monkeys, orangutans) to "roaaar" (tigers, big cats, and an elephant seal, and sharks) to "bee bee bee" (small birds, emperor penguins) to "walrus" to "doh tee" (goats, sheep) to "bear!", he has a great time identifying different animals in the book.
<br><br><p>The photographs are stunning. The image of the lone polar bear lit by the evening "magic light" is worth the price of the book alone. What's even better is Art's photo commentary. Each photo (or collection of photos) has a description of the circumstances around the time it was created, as well as a photo-geek summary of how he shot the image. I can't recommend this book highly enough.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
